messages.message: Hey, I find that this kind of output happens a lot. I tend to see it when a reasoning prompt fails to output a table or JSON, or a cleaning function is applied incorrectly to a table. In this case (screenshot) I actually expect the clean to fail, but passing back "||" as a response in any these situations seems like a bad way to handle this compared to "Empty" or "No Value" or something
cc @CJ @danny.lan should the frontend check for this empty piping and return “No value found”
i’ve seen this before too btw
i mean, i think this is _technically_ correct markdown table, just an empty one???
yup, I think in the cases where we have a list or table type if the markdown is an empty list/table we should return “No value found”
the current output that Hamish is reporting here is pretty confusing for a general user
i think this should be fixed in 24.24 per https://instabase.atlassian.net/browse/INSIGHTS-6579 since @Vishnu mentioned so here (https://instabase.atlassian.net/browse/EPD-2102?focusedCommentId=54985)
